messages.content: 9-1-1, what's your emergency?
I don't know the exact address, but it's near Spartan Avenue. We took a left at the light.
Sir, can you tell me where you are?
I don't know the name of the road.
Are you in Loveland?
No, it's near Bertha High School. You turn left from Spartan Avenue.
Okay, so you're off Spartan Avenue near Bertha High School?
Yeah, take a left there.
All right. And what is the problem?
There's been a serious car wreck.
Okay, are there any injuries?
Yes.
Is it on the corner or on the street?
It's on the street.
How many vehicles are involved?
Three.
Is anyone pinned inside their vehicle?
No.
Okay, we will get help on the way. Are there confirmed injuries?
Yes, I promise.
They're already on the way. They'll be there shortly.
Thank you.
You're welcome. Bye.
9-1-1, what's your emergency?
There's an accident. We just got there and we're on our way.
Where are you at?
We were on our way to someone's house.
Where are you right now?
Guys, where are we? Two of our guys aren't moving, but they're still breathing. Someone just hold us.
I need to know where you're at before I can get anyone to you.
We're coming off Spartan Avenue, near the hill.
Are you near Bertha High School?
Yeah, we're just off Bertha High.
Okay, and tell me the condition of everyone. How many people are hurt?
One of our guys is running around, stressed. Tyler isn't moving. They were trying to fix the flat tire and someone hit them from behind.
How many people are hurt?
Two of them aren't moving. They're breathing, but barely.
Out of seven people there, how many are hurt?
Two are severely hurt; they're on the ground. The rest are fine.
Okay, they're coming. I just have a few more questions for you. Hold on.
I can't get out.
I need you to check on the people not moving. Make sure they are still breathing.
We can't get up; Tyler is completely out.
Is Tyler the one who was changing the tire?
Yes. They were behind the truck and got hit.
Did they get hit as well?
Yes, I think Tyler actually got hit.
Okay, check on Tyler for me. Let me know his condition.
He’s not responding.
I want someone to stay with him and make sure he continues to breathe. Is he still breathing?
Yes, he is still breathing.
Okay, I am going to keep you on the line until help arrives. Keep checking on Tyler.
Okay.
Do not move him unless he is in immediate danger.
Where exactly are you guys from Bertha High School? Are you on Spartan or another road?
Hello? Let me call back. The other caller is probably in better shape to talk.
Okay, we will stay with it. Help is on the way. Bye.
